context: Rare books are found in several Yale collections. <a3_0><b8_0>The Beinecke Rare Book Library<b8_0/><a3_0/> has a large collection of rare books and manuscripts. <a0_0><b4_0>The Harvey Cushing/John Hay Whitney Medical Library<b4_0/><a0_0/> includes important historical medical texts, including an impressive collection of rare books, as well as historical medical instruments. <a1_0><b5_0>The Lewis Walpole Library<b5_0/><a1_0/> contains the largest collection of 18th‑century British literary works. <a2_0><b6_0><b7_0>The Elizabethan Club<b7_0/><b6_0/><a2_0/>, technically a private organization, makes its Elizabethan folios and first editions available to qualified researchers through Yale.
